---
description: Engineering completion standard
alwaysApply: true
---

- Preserve architectural boundaries while delivering the smallest complete milestone.
- Make errors explicit and actionable; do not silently discard failed work.
- Test observable behavior rather than implementation details.
- Keep default tests deterministic and independent of live provider credentials.
- Update documentation when an intentional design decision changes the architecture or a public contract.
- Surface unresolved architectural conflicts instead of encoding an arbitrary choice in code.
